                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.38/84</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Blanchard</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>. <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-06-17T09:00:00-04:49">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 17, 1916, 9 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your June 15, 4 p.m. Minister for Foreign Affairs states that Minister Ménos has
                    been instructed by telegraph to conduct and conclude stated negotiations.
                    Similar full powers as given Commission have been forwarded by mail to him.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Blanchard</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
